cgXKBdwlmimcKTmInr5PbxasF53RqPcXsSEaGBBh9Xgy3DK2SEOnl9dX8GKZhabL3ZpwQ4EdCXBFn0ZhCbfBGV9STcYYb6rKjbrCDvBTJ6MM7pqjl1pQCNdPnK52uhy0JSoIX40hE0dS2JesDBjzsaYatA_Qf6cKf_ZxxUOJC4fgL_tYzTIj8XZ43fciflKKVSuJhSE0jrX6WJ90o1-ckDr-20OP-H2d_RsHxHUeITjQPUV2FaGkaXEtA2F9VLeFVdFIokZmNFVpSfSyVcS5MTVR3Uotx2sXQkvj1ygjz7YUsXFAcK6u06ifXhzJ5G02QmIzr5q1e9s3LBZ2BguoaeqbCdQJNN7M1wG0l1PCurQRNubbet1lMWmO_r_oA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native test performance**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the native test that's generated from conditional metadata should pass successfully. However, I wonder if using Class.forName in a native image requires the class to be registered first. Can it load classes that are already present? If I'm calling Class.forName for an application class with a constant, does it handle dynamic variables from a file? I should note that the metadata generated by the agent should also include UDP. Good!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing flow**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to test in the repository before the agent runs, but it seems like this flow isn’t meant to be executed on our end. I think I should ensure that there’s no version hardcoding, and instead, use directory listing. I’ll need to create a file, possibly add a copyright header, and import AssertJ. Plus, I should include the tempdir annotation and ensure I’m using a public class. I'll also want to avoid direct reflection. Time to check styles in other files!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_p34I5Fwy4SgUpcMm5uDwPGwb|fc_07471a0350bb41d50169f26a15ff248192b22fbb76dc825a5e", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jgroups/jgroups/XMLSchemaGeneratorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_jgroups.jgroups;\n\nimport org.jgroups.util.XMLSchemaGenerator;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class XMLSchemaGeneratorTest {\n    private static final String PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_PATH = \"org/jgroups/protocols\";\n    private static final String PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_NAME = \"org.jgroups.protocols\";\n    private static final String PROTOCOL_CLASS_FILE = \"UDP.class\";\n\n    @TempDir\n    private Path tempDir;\n\n    @Test\n    void generatesSchemaFromProtocolDirectoryResource() throws Exception {\n        Path protocolDirectory = tempDir.resolve(PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_PATH);\n        Files.createDirectories(protocolDirectory);\n        Files.write(protocolDirectory.resolve(PROTOCOL_CLASS_FILE), new byte[0]);\n\n        ClassLoader previousLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new ProtocolDirectoryClassLoader(previousLoader, protocolDirectory));\n        try {\n            XMLSchemaGenerator.main(new String[] {\"-o\", tempDir.toString()});\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousLoader);\n        }\n\n        List<Path> generatedSchemas;\n        try (var files = Files.list(tempDir)) {\n            generatedSchemas = files\n                .filter(path -> path.getFileName().toString().endsWith(\".xsd\"))\n                .toList();\n        }\n        assertThat(generatedSchemas).hasSize(1);\n\n        String schema = Files.readString(generatedSchemas.get(0), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        assertThat(schema).contains(\"<xs:element name=\\\"UDP\\\">\");\n        assertThat(schema).contains(\"name=\\\"bind_addr\\\"\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void discoversConcreteProtocolClassesFromDirectoryResource() throws Exception {\n        Path protocolDirectory = tempDir.resolve(PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_PATH);\n        Files.createDirectories(protocolDirectory);\n        Files.write(protocolDirectory.resolve(PROTOCOL_CLASS_FILE), new byte[0]);\n\n        ClassLoader previousLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new ProtocolDirectoryClassLoader(previousLoader, protocolDirectory));\n        try {\n            assertThat(XMLSchemaGenerator.getClasses(org.jgroups.stack.Protocol.class, PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_NAME))\n                .extracting(Class::getName)\n                .contains(\"org.jgroups.protocols.UDP\");\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ProtocolDirectoryClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final Path protocolDirectory;\n\n        private ProtocolDirectoryClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, Path protocolDirectory) {\n            super(parent);\n            this.protocolDirectory = protocolDirectory;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String name) {\n            if (PROTOCOL_PACKAGE_PATH.equals(name)) {\n                try {\n                    return protocolDirectory.toUri().toURL();\n                } catch (IOException e) {\n                    throw new IllegalStateException(\"Could not expose protocol test directory\", e);\n                }\n            }\n            return super.getResource(name);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jgroups/jgroups/XMLSchemaGeneratorTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_jgroups.jgroups;\\n\\nimport